Note:
BUILD TARGET - Per-Target Build Specification (Tier 1)

Describes one buildable artifact emitted from a Runa package. A package
may declare multiple targets - a library, several binaries, tests,
benchmarks, and examples - each with their own entry point and feature
selection. Mirrors the [[bin]] / [[example]] / [[test]] / [[bench]] /
[lib] sections of Cargo.toml.

Layout (BuildTarget, 56 bytes):
  offset  0 : kind         (8 bytes, see TARGET_* constants)
  offset  8 : name         (8 bytes, String pointer)
  offset 16 : entry_path   (8 bytes, String pointer to source file)
  offset 24 : features     (8 bytes, List<String> pointer or 0)
  offset 32 : dependencies (8 bytes, List<String> pointer or 0)
  offset 40 : crate_type   (8 bytes, String pointer or 0 - lib/dylib/staticlib/cdylib)
  offset 48 : required     (8 bytes, 0 = optional, 1 = required - skipped if features missing)

References:
  - Cargo build target ........ https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/cargo-targets.html
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Let TARGET_SIZE be 56

Let TARGET_BINARY be 1
Let TARGET_LIBRARY be 2
Let TARGET_TEST be 3
Let TARGET_BENCHMARK be 4
Let TARGET_EXAMPLE be 5

@Reasoning
Allocate a BuildTarget with mandatory kind + name + entry_path and empty
feature / dependency selectors.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate the 56-byte record, populate the three mandatory slots, set
required=1 (the default), leave optional slots NULL.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null inputs or invalid kind.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "target_create" takes kind as Integer, name as Integer, entry_path as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If entry_path is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If kind is less than TARGET_BINARY:
        Return 0
    End If
    If kind is greater than TARGET_EXAMPLE:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let t be proc allocate from Layout with TARGET_SIZE
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 0, kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 8, name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 16, entry_path
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 48, 1
    Return t
End Process

@Reasoning
Free the target record without touching subordinate strings or lists.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the record.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must not access the pointer after destroy.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "target_destroy" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let features be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 24
    If features is not equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with features
    End If
    Let deps be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 32
    If deps is not equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with deps
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with t
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the target kind discriminator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null - distinct from any valid TARGET_* kind.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "target_kind" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the target's logical name (used as the artifact filename).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "target_name" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the entry-point source path.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 16.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "target_entry_path" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 16
End Process

@Reasoning
Attach a feature-name list to the target. Replaces any existing list.
The caller transfers ownership.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Free the existing list if non-null, then store the new pointer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) for the eviction. Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Strings inside the list are not freed; the caller retains their
ownership unless they were previously transferred to the list.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "target_set_features" takes t as Integer, features as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 24
    If old is not equal to 0:
        proc list_destroy from List with old
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 24, features
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Expose the feature list.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 24.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 if no list attached.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "target_features" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 24
End Process

@Reasoning
Toggle the required flag - if 1, the target build fails when its feature
gates are unsatisfied; if 0, the target is silently skipped.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Coerce input to 0 or 1 and store at offset 48.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "target_set_required" takes t as Integer, required as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let v be 0
    If required is equal to 1:
        Set v to 1
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with t, 48, v
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
True if the target is mandatory.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load offset 48.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "target_is_required" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with t, 48
End Process
